                <Paragraph FontSize="14.6666666666667" FontFamily="Palatino Linotype" Margin="0" TextAlignment="Justify">
                    <Run FontSize="12" Text="Texas Instruments Inc. (TI) manufactures, markets and sells high-technology components and systems used in the commercial electronic and electrical equipment industry, primarily for industrial and consumer markets. TI has three principal businesses: Semiconductor, Sensors and Controls, and Educational and Productivity Solutions. Semiconductor designs, manufactures and sells integrated circuits. Its core products include analog integrated circuits and digital signal processors. Sensors and Controls sell custom-designed sensors, controls and radio frequency identification systems. Educational and Productivity Solutions is a supplier of graphing handheld calculators and other calculators. The Company's largest geographic markets are in Asia, Europe, the United States and Japan."/>
